en_160432_0	The Geology Department of Peradeniya University states that Gohagoda garbage mount in Kandy could catch fire or explore at any moment.
en_160432_1	Professor Athula Senarathna told our news team that the authorities should take remedial action immediately.
en_160432_2	He said plenty of methane that had been accumulated inside the garbage mount could lead to an explosion or fire.
en_160432_3	At the same time Provincial Council and Local Government Ministry has imitated a special investigation to ascertain whether there is any crack in the garbage mount and any gases are emanating.
